This Agreement is made effective as of February 14, 2003, by and between AHRE, of 200 Park
Avenue South, New York, New York 10003, and Fernandez Translating & Consulting Services,
of 190 Lexington Avenue, Passaic, New Jersey 07055.
In this Agreement, the party who is contracting to receive services shall be referred to as "AHRC"
and the party who will be providing the services shall be referred to as "FT&CS "
FT&CS has a background in Labor/Management Relations Consulting and is willing to provide
services to AHRC based on this background.
AHRC desires to have services provided by FT&CS.
Therefore, the parties agree as follows:
1. DESCRIPTION OF SERVICES. Beginning on February 14, 2003, FT&CS will provide the
following services, (collectively, the "Services"): Labor/Management Relations Consulting
Fernandez also agrees, as a material term of this Agreement, that he shall fully comply with all the
standards of conduct mandated by the National Labor Relations Act, the Labor Management
Relations Act, the Labor-Management Reporting Disclosure Act, AND ALL APPLICABLE FEDERAL,
2. PAYMENT. AHRC will pay a fee to FT&CS for the Services in the amount of $150.00.
This fee shall be payable on a per hour basis, per consultant. Payment will be due upon receipt of
invoice. Invoice will be delivered on a weekly basis. All other related expenses including but not
limited to - One way travel, materials, preparation of documents, translations etc will be paid
full by AHRC. Upon termination of this Agreement, payments under this paragraph shall cease;
provided, however, that FT&CS shall be entitled to payments for periods or partial periods that
occurred prior to the date of termination and for which FT&CS has not yet been paid.
3. TERM/TERMINATION. This Agreement shall. terminate automatically upon completion by
FT&CS of the Services required by this Agreement. IDDITIONALLY, FITHER PARTY MAY
TERMINATE THIS AGREEMENT UPON WRITTEN DOTICE.
4. RELATIONSHIP OF PARTIES. It is understood by the parties that FT&CS is an
independent contractor with respect to AHRC, and not an employee of AHRC. AHRC will not
provide fringe benefits, including health insurance benefits, paid vacation, or any other employee
benefit, for the benefit of FT&CS.
5. EMPLOYEES. FT&CS's employees, if any, who perform services for AHRC under this
Agreement shall also be bound by the provisions of this Agreement.
6. NOTICES. All notices required or permitted under this Agreement shall be in writing and
shall be deemed delivered when delivered in person or deposited in the United States mail,
Such address may be changed from time to time by either party by providing written notice to the
other in the manner set forth above.
7. ENTIRE AGREEMENT. This Agreement contains the entire agreement of the parties and
there are no other promises or conditions in any other agreement whether oral or written. This
Agreement supersedes any prior written or oral agreements between the parties.
8. AMENDMENT. This Agreement may be modified or amended if the amendment is made in
writing and is signed by both parties.
9. SEVERABILITY. If any provision of this Agreement shall be held to be invalid or
unenforceable for any reason, the remaining provisions shall continue to be valid and enforceable.
If a court finds that any provision of this Agreement is invalid or unenforceable, but that by
limiting such provision it would become valid and enforceable, then such provision shall be
deemed to be written, construed, and enforced as so limited.
10. WAIVER OF CONTRACTUAL RIGHT. The failure of either party to enforce any
provision of this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or limitation of that party's right to
subsequently enforce and compel strict compliance with every provision of this Agreement.
11. APPLICABLELAW. This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of New
12. INDEMNIFICATION. FT & CS shall fully indemnify and hold AHRC, its officers, directors,
employees, agents and affiliates harmless from and against any and all loss, damage, injury, liability, claims, actions,
proceedings, costs, fees, disbursements and expenses of whatever kind or nature, including but not limited to legal
fees and disbursements, which any of them may suffer or incur as a result of or in connection with personal injury,
property damage and willful misconduct leading to a finding of violation of criminal law.
